From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gnoblin Developers <gnoblin@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 16:10:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] tooling: expose feature variables in uninstalled pkg-config

gnome-shell reads Mutter's typelibdir and have_* pkg-config variables
while configuring. Meson's generated uninstalled .pc files only include
variables listed in uninstalled_variables, so local builds that point
gnome-shell at a patched, uninstalled Mutter fail during regeneration.
---
 src/meson.build | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/meson.build b/src/meson.build
index 61f2b76..3adf6f4 100644
--- a/src/meson.build
+++ b/src/meson.build
@@ -1379,6 +1379,15 @@ pkg.generate(libmutter,
     'have_wayland=@0@'.format(have_wayland),
     'have_fonts=@0@'.format(have_fonts),
   ],
+  uninstalled_variables: [
+    'apiversion=' + libmutter_api_version,
+    'girdir=${prefix}/src',
+    'typelibdir=${prefix}/src',
+    'have_x11=@0@'.format(have_x11),
+    'have_x11_client=@0@'.format(have_x11_client),
+    'have_wayland=@0@'.format(have_wayland),
+    'have_fonts=@0@'.format(have_fonts),
+  ],
   install_dir: pcdir,
 )
 
-- 
2.50.0
